{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d67734", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "62c481f001514d218a7934d1", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "question": {"text": "<p>Given below are two statements : One is labelled as Assertion (A) and the other is labelled as Reason (R).</p><p><strong>Assertion (A) :</strong> In an uniform magnetic field, speed and energy remains the same for a moving charged particle.</p><p><strong>Reason (R): </strong>Moving charged particle experiences magnetic force perpendicular to its direction of motion.</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "I8ra2", "text": "Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of Assertion.", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "6csyZ", "text": "Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is NOT the correct explanation of Assertion.", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "5BPYF", "text": "Assertion is true but Reason is false.", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "oP0d8", "text": "Assertion is false but Reason is true.", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>The force experienced by the charge particle is perpendicular to the instantaneous velocity at all instants as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p><p>Hence, the magnetic force cannot bring any change in the speed of the charged particle. Since, the speed&nbsp;remains constant, the kinetic energy also remains constant.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ00210249", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61602420ae6dd863a9d1d7d8", "6160241f1a832a8dea12fbf0", "616024236098c3dc0cc3e764", "61602422b42cfaef18219875", "616024227e2ba4496fdd4552", "61964c8c8d7ade9f02022966", "61c08987636555dc34527e11", "61e7bd70643383b6c26bfb1d", "61964c8e8811f774a40dd9f1", "62962123b040395dcc21a751", "629f3a9143c2c00ea1d2f857", "629109edc3391b7808eb05af", "61bb820fdb486fa25580e4bd", "629f390c27047111eccefe03", "64eb06c03118f713ecfef077", "66d5853aa75f05ee8564f568", "67921d601d5b5072da5e9a88", "67fdff4f378e1624ea7b6a03", "6809202a3a10446a207fded7"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}